      "rationale": "Four-level mesh convergence study conducted; GCI values of 1.8% (stiffness) and 3.2% (peak stress) computed between fine and very-fine meshes. Richardson extrapolation confirms asymptotic convergence. Medium mesh (0.9 mm) selected for validation runs as it satisfies GCI < 5% with acceptable runtime. Required level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Force and displacement residuals converge below 1e-6 relative tolerance; energy balance error < 0.1%.",
      "rationale": "All simulations converged with force residuals below 1e-7 and energy balance errors below 0.05%. No solver warnings or divergence events recorded across the 11-construct ensemble. Required level 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation setup reviewed by independent analyst; boundary conditions and material assignments verified against COU specification document.",
      "rationale": "An independent senior analyst reviewed the model setup checklist covering geometry import, contact definitions, boundary conditions, and material property assignments. All items confirmed consistent with the COU specification. Required level 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Linear elastic model form justified by experimental evidence that yield occurs at large displacements; contact formulation validated against closed-form solutions.",
      "rationale": "The pedicle screw construct remains predominantly elastic below yield; experimental load-displacement curves confirm linear behavior up to 85% of yield load. Augmented Lagrange frictional contact (μ=0.3) validated against Hertz contact benchmarks. Geometric nonlinearity included via large-deformation formulation. Required level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties (Ti-6Al-4V and UHMWPE block) sourced from ASTM-certified coupon testing; geometric dimensions from CMM measurements of production screws.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V elastic modulus (114 GPa) and yield strength (880 MPa) from ASTM E8 tensile testing of production-lot coupons. UHMWPE block modulus from supplier data sheet corroborated by compression testing. All 11 construct geometries digitized via CMM; nominal CAD used for FEA with dimensional tolerances captured in sensitivity analysis. Required level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N=11 production-representative constructs tested; sample traceability documented; dimensional inspection confirms conformance to drawing.",
      "rationale": "Eleven non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs assembled from production-lot components. Each construct dimensionally inspected by CMM prior to testing. Lot traceability records maintained. Sample size sufficient for statistical comparison at the required confidence level. Required level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of clinically relevant loading rates and environmental conditions; at minimum two test conditions evaluated.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed under a single set of ASTM F1717 conditions (ambient, quasi-static 5 mm/min). Clinical loading variability across patient weight and activity level not captured by a single test condition. Achieved level 2 is below the required level 3; this gap is acknowledged and accepted given that ASTM F1717 is the regulatory standard and no alternative multi-condition data exist for this construct geometry."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA boundary conditions (fixture geometry, loading point, constraint locations) demonstrably equivalent to physical test setup.",
      "rationale": "ASTM F1717 fixture geometry modeled from engineering drawings of the actual test fixtures used at both laboratories. Loading point and constraint locations confirmed by photographic documentation. Friction coefficient at fixture interfaces measured and applied in FEA. Required level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric E/uval < 1.96 for all three QoIs; percent difference < 10%.",
      "rationale": "All three QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) satisfy E/uval < 1.96 and percent difference < 10%. Validation uncertainty uval computed per ASME V&V 20 combining experimental standard uncertainty and simulation numerical uncertainty. Required level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs directly map to regulatory submission requirements and clinical failure modes.",
      "rationale": "Stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three QoIs mandated by ASTM F1717 and referenced in FDA guidance for spinal implant submissions. These QoIs are directly linked to clinical failure modes (fatigue fracture precursor yielding, construct loosening). Required level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
